# Logos/images under this folder are already served with no authentication (plain static files),
# so this doesn't expose anything new - it only lets browser JS (running on a different origin,
# e.g. the Vite dev server) read the pixel data it can already display in an <img> tag. Needed so
# the frontend can embed the school logo into exported PDFs (jsPDF draws images via <canvas>,
# which throws a SecurityError on cross-origin images without this header).
<IfModule mod_headers.c>
    Header set Access-Control-Allow-Origin "*"
</IfModule>
